The article announces several nominations and appointments:

1. Jonathan Moak from Virginia has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of the Army for Financial Management and Comptroller. He currently serves as the Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Army for Financial Management and Comptroller.

2. Charles W. Cook Jr. from Mississippi has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Directors of the Tennessee Valley Authority. He is currently the Chairman of Bandwidth Infrastructure Holdings, LLC.

3. Ilan Berman from Maryland has been nominated to be a Member of the International Broadcasting Advisory Board for a term of three years. He currently serves as Senior Vice President at the American Foreign Policy Council.

4. Michael Finkel from New Jersey has been nominated to be a Director of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation. He currently serves as Director and Senior Counsel at the Global Investment Bank Societe Generale.

5. Jo-Ann Chase from Virginia has been nominated to be a Member of the President's Advisory Commission on Hispanic Prosperity.

6. John T. McNabb II from North Carolina has been nominated to be a Member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council.